I'll do my best to explain
uhm... everything about auras..
They are a way of modifying roles with additional benefits or drawbacks

So you can have a seer who has an aura called Tenacious - this means they cannot be role-blocked. Normally seers can be blocked but if the moderator wants to make a seer that can't, they can give them this aura.
Some auras are assigned at the start, some come from in-game effects or items

For example, some items can "cripple" a role which gives them the crippled aura which makes it harder for them to use any abilities "further away" from them in the list as they will have a greater chance of being role-blocked
Some auras are visiible to the player, some are not (tenacious is not visible to you, so you wouldn't know if you had it)
There are some roles and items that can check for auras, such as the aura seer, aura diviner and vibra rune
They are essentially checking for this extra modifier on players
Some items give off auras simply by holding them
The auras also communicate extra information about what's happening in the game, for those who can see them (like an aura seer)
e.g if someone has the rats on them from the Vermin Talisman, they have an aura applied to them called "OverrunByRats" which could be seen by an aura seer
ohh but otherwise the player wouldn't know they have that aura and its effects?
It depends on the aura but yes
alr, tysm!!
Some auras you know about because the game tells you
e.g if you have a "Tough" aura, you are told
big props to sox
Some auras you will know you have because you know the status
